
NAME
       ipcmk - create various ipc resources

SYNOPSIS
       ipcmk -h
       ipcmk [-M size] [-S nsems] [-Q] [-p mode]

DESCRIPTION
       ipcmk  allows  you  to create shared memory segments, message queues or semaphore
       arrays.

OPTIONS
       Resources may be specified as follows:

       -M size
              shared memory segment of size size

       -S nsems
              semaphore array with nsems elements

       -Q     message queue

       Other options

       -p mode
              permission for the resource (default is 0644)

       -h     display a short help message and exit

SEE ALSO
       ipcrm(1), ipcs(1)
